basic.floral_language:
Impatiens hawkeri 
Floriography: beautiful, vivid, charm
The flower of Impatiens walleriana resembles a butterfly with multiple colors, such as white, pink, purple, and red. Leaves green, lanceolate shape. The flower and leaves can be mashed, wrapped around girl's fingernails to paint fresh colors, like henna.
Impatiens walleriana likes ample sunlight, but properly shade in summer. Flowers in June-October with a period flower viewing for 1-2 months.
basic.blooming: Flowering period July-October, viewing period 1-2 months

maintenance.watering: Water thoroughly when soil is dry, water daily in summer
maintenance.fertilization: Dilute fertilizers following instructions, apply 1-2 times monthly in spring and summer
maintenance.pruning: Remove old, diseased and dead leaves timely
